OL,3,CFormer firefighter handed community
OL,4,Corder for racially aggravated
OL,5,Charassment
OL,7,FSuggitt initially denied the charge,
OL,8,Fsaying the comments were intended as
OL,9,F'fun' but later changed his plea to
OL,10,Fguilty.
OL,12,FOn sentencing, the judge warned
OL,13,FSuggitt that he could have been served
OL,14,Fa jail sentence for his behaviour.
OL,16,FSuggitt was given a twelve-month
OL,17,Fcommunity order, ordered him to pay
OL,18,F#500 pounds compensation and issued
OL,19,Fwith a restraining order.
